  "text": "Children are a special category of patients. The lack of suitable specific pediatric formulations often leads to the use of extemporaneous preparations obtained starting from the dosage form for adults, by dilution of liquid formulations, opening or capsules or finely grinding of tablets, administered as suspensions. However, such manipulations give rise to a series of disadvantages, including in particular minor dosing accuracy, unknown and variable bioavailability, poor compliance for both children and caregivers, and lack of data about the preparation stability [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
